c371g2.ltc_safety.local

Class ConcernWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • c371g2.ltc_safety.local.ConcernWrapper
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<ConcernWrapper>

    public class ConcernWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Comparable<ConcernWrapper>, java.io.Serializable
    Class that contains all fields in the Concern class, but in common data types. The OwnerToken did not need to be converted into an atomic data type because it only contains String.
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
    Invariants:
    - All fields are non-null. - concernType.length() > 0
    History Properties:
    All fields are final except for the OwnerToken. For a given instance of ConcernWrapper, each of those fields is only initialized via the constructor.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ConcernWrapper

        public ConcernWrapper(@NonNull
                      Concern concern,
                      @NonNull
                      OwnerToken token)
        Constructor for ConcernWrapper. Takes a Concern as input and generates a ConcernWrapper.
        Parameters:
        concern - The concern received from the backend via the Client API
        token - The token that proves this concern was submitted on this device.
        preconditions:
        concern and token are non-null.
        modifies:
        Initializes all fields in this class. Fields corresponding to the inputs not provided by the reporter are initialized to an empty string.
